{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778376815538,"sessionID":"ses_1f07bcac7ffePC6ryWfpJezQfx","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_35lzL4QXnHHPXfPPxaQctLb4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+# Design Pattern Notes for GO:0061852\n+\n+Issue: https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31935\n+\n+## Scope\n+\n+The requested change updates an existing cellular component term:\n+\n+- Rename `GO:0061852` from `retrograde transporter complex, Golgi to ER` to `retrograde cargo receptor complex, Golgi to ER`.\n+- Add `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex` as the superclass.\n+- Update the text definition so it begins with `Cargo receptor complex...` and uses GO's standard American spelling `recognizes`.\n+- Preserve the former primary label as a broad synonym, because the old wording is broader than the cargo receptor complex being described.\n+\n+## Relevant Pattern And Precedent\n+\n+The relevant documented pattern is `src/design_patterns/protein_complex_by_activity.yaml`, which defines protein complexes by a molecular function using:\n+\n+```obo\n+intersection_of: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\n+intersection_of: capable_of <molecular function>\n+```\n+\n+`GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex` already follows this pattern and is defined as:\n+\n+```obo\n+name: cargo receptor complex\n+def: \"Any protein complex that is part of a membrane and which functions as a cargo receptor.\" [PMID:27903609]\n+intersection_of: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\n+intersection_of: capable_of GO:0038024 ! cargo receptor activity\n+intersection_of: part_of GO:0016020 ! membrane\n+```\n+\n+## Design Decision\n+\n+For `GO:0061852`, the issue asks for a new asserted superclass, not a new equivalence axiom. I therefore plan to add an `is_a: GO:0062137 ! cargo receptor complex` assertion and not add any new `intersection_of` logical definition. This avoids over-specifying the term while aligning it with the requested parent.\n+\n+Because `GO:0062137` is already a protein-containing complex and membrane-associated cargo receptor complex, the previous asserted parent `GO:1990351 transporter complex` should be replaced rather than retained as an additional asserted `is_a`, consistent with GO guidance to avoid unnecessary multiple asserted parents.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+# Design Pattern Notes for GO:0061852\n+\n+Issue: https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31935\n+\n+## Scope\n+\n+The requested change updates an existing cellular component term:\n+\n+- Rename `GO:0061852` from `retrograde transporter complex, Golgi to ER` to `retrograde cargo receptor complex, Golgi to ER`.\n+- Add `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex` as the superclass.\n+- Update the text definition so it begins with `Cargo receptor complex...` and uses GO's standard American spelling `recognizes`.\n+- Preserve the former primary label as a broad synonym, because the old wording is broader than the cargo receptor complex being described.\n+\n+## Relevant Pattern And Precedent\n+\n+The relevant documented pattern is `src/design_patterns/protein_complex_by_activity.yaml`, which defines protein complexes by a molecular function using:\n+\n+```obo\n+intersection_of: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\n+intersection_of: capable_of <molecular function>\n+```\n+\n+`GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex` already follows this pattern and is defined as:\n+\n+```obo\n+name: cargo receptor complex\n+def: \"Any protein complex that is part of a membrane and which functions as a cargo receptor.\" [PMID:27903609]\n+intersection_of: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\n+intersection_of: capable_of GO:0038024 ! cargo receptor activity\n+intersection_of: part_of GO:0016020 ! membrane\n+```\n+\n+## Design Decision\n+\n+For `GO:0061852`, the issue asks for a new asserted superclass, not a new equivalence axiom. I therefore plan to add an `is_a: GO:0062137 ! cargo receptor complex` assertion and not add any new `intersection_of` logical definition. This avoids over-specifying the term while aligning it with the requested parent.\n+\n+Because `GO:0062137` is already a protein-containing complex and membrane-associated cargo receptor complex, the previous asserted parent `GO:1990351 transporter complex` should be replaced rather than retained as an additional asserted `is_a`, consistent with GO guidance to avoid unnecessary multiple asserted parents.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","relativePath":"DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+# Design Pattern Notes for GO:0061852\n+\n+Issue: https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31935\n+\n+## Scope\n+\n+The requested change updates an existing cellular component term:\n+\n+- Rename `GO:0061852` from `retrograde transporter complex, Golgi to ER` to `retrograde cargo receptor complex, Golgi to ER`.\n+- Add `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex` as the superclass.\n+- Update the text definition so it begins with `Cargo receptor complex...` and uses GO's standard American spelling `recognizes`.\n+- Preserve the former primary label as a broad synonym, because the old wording is broader than the cargo receptor complex being described.\n+\n+## Relevant Pattern And Precedent\n+\n+The relevant documented pattern is `src/design_patterns/protein_complex_by_activity.yaml`, which defines protein complexes by a molecular function using:\n+\n+```obo\n+intersection_of: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\n+intersection_of: capable_of <molecular function>\n+```\n+\n+`GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex` already follows this pattern and is defined as:\n+\n+```obo\n+name: cargo receptor complex\n+def: \"Any protein complex that is part of a membrane and which functions as a cargo receptor.\" [PMID:27903609]\n+intersection_of: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\n+intersection_of: capable_of GO:0038024 ! cargo receptor activity\n+intersection_of: part_of GO:0016020 ! membrane\n+```\n+\n+## Design Decision\n+\n+For `GO:0061852`, the issue asks for a new asserted superclass, not a new equivalence axiom. I therefore plan to add an `is_a: GO:0062137 ! cargo receptor complex` assertion and not add any new `intersection_of` logical definition. This avoids over-specifying the term while aligning it with the requested parent.\n+\n+Because `GO:0062137` is already a protein-containing complex and membrane-associated cargo receptor complex, the previous asserted parent `GO:1990351 transporter complex` should be replaced rather than retained as an additional asserted `is_a`, consistent with GO guidance to avoid unnecessary multiple asserted parents.\n","additions":37,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","time":{"start":1778376815529,"end":1778376815536}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a9192ff595e1f630169ffe06a2d9c819d8d8ed6e8509ee4a4"}},"id":"prt_e0f849edc0019RK6XQMnGcRFWl","sessionID":"ses_1f07bcac7ffePC6ryWfpJezQfx","messageID":"msg_e0f849b3f001zRFgdRT6Gj0nPT"}}
